The principles of quality management  of an organization   that provides or arranges social services, and the quality of management; manager's responsibilities when assuring the quality of social services. Process management and description of processes. Standards of services, management policy, quality control and supervision in the organizations providing social services.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to expand the learners' knowledge about the principles of quality management and explain their applications in social services. The course handles the principles of quality management and the best methods of measuring and assessing service quality. Attention is paid to noticing customer-orientation and the need of including target groups, process-centred and systematic approach to quality, and the need for decision-making based on facts and constant improvement. The overview of quality management tools is given.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) knows the basics of quality management and mechanisms of quality assurance of social services; 2) describes the processes related to the provision of social services; 3) orients oneself in legislation regulating the quality of social services; 4) navigates in the legal acts that regulate the quality of social services; 5) implements the principles of quality management when planning social services.
